724037f-a.title: Manhattan: Washington Square South - Sullivan Street
724037f-a.text:
07-40 Washington Square South, west from Sullivan to Macdougal
Streets.
Compare with Brown Brothers' photo of this block in 1905, a year or
two after Sullivan Street had been cut through from West Third
Street. As shown here, the buildings are shortly to be remodelled
into apartments and studios.
About 1922.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.
